&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A) Brief Details about this Program:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IEEE--PES/IAS/PELS Jt. Chapter, IEEE-Hyderabad Section, is organizing this Professional Development Program (PDP). We invite Industry Professionals, Young Professionals / Faculty in Academic Institutions / Research Scholars and PG &amp;amp; UG Students .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This PDP is designed to be beneficial to practicing engineers from industry/ consultants/ faculty from engineering colleges/ students / research scholars who are working/ interested in the area of Power Systems, Power Electronics, Utility Grids/ Microgrids and Battery Energy Storage Systems. Also, this PDP will create opportunities for research, better teaching and introduction of new courses in this field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract of the above PDP: Workshop :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The modern power systems are changing fast with large scale deployment of Renewable Energy Sources (RES) based power Plants using Solar PV and Wind Power.&amp;nbsp; This is resulting in Micro grids which operate as stand alone type feeding a group of local loads and another type which are also connected to a large utility grid in addition to feeding the local loads. Battery based Energy Storage Systems (BESS) in combination with Bi-Directional Power Electronic Convertor are being used to mitigate the limitations of discontinuous energy supply form RES like Solar Power Plants and Wind Turbine-Generator Power Plants. All these are creating new challenges and opportunities in developing new technologies and operation of the Power systems at various levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many industries / utilities and academic institutions are extensively working to solve various issues related to Utility Grids/ Microgrids/ BESS/ Bi-Directional Power Electronic Convertors. Considerable R&amp;amp;D work is in progress and this area and it is resulting in advanced New Products. Many of these developed products are already commercially deployed and are working energy efficiently giving reliable operation. Today, both AC or DC type Micro-grids are in operation and also under further development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This PDP is designed to focus on creating know-how/ know-why on various aspects Utility Grids/ Microgrids including issues related to their topology/ interconnection/ grid integration, battery energy storage systems/ Bi-Directional Power Electronic Convertor technologies, local generation and power flow control.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brief details of the Major Topics that will be covered in the above Program are as follows:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The focus will be on topics like :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solar PV based Power Plants and their Power Electronic Converters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Battery Energy Storage Systems--- Future Opportunities &amp;amp; Challenges- in Utility &amp;amp; Microgrids.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bi-Directional Power Electronic Converters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Various Issues related to System Design/ System Integration/ Grid Integration/ Sub-Systems and various issues related to their Design, Selection and Sizing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Energy Management and Control in Utility Grids / Microgrids.&lt;/li&gt;
