&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A) Brief Details about this Program :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IEEE--PES/IAS/PELS Jt. Chapter, IEEE-Hyderabad Section, is organizing this Professional Development Program. We invite Industry Professionals, Young Professionals / Faculty in Academic Institutions and Research Scholars/ Students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Distinguished/ eminent persons who contributed to innovations, applications of &amp;nbsp;technology for the advancement of our society, are invited by our Jt. Chapter for a Distinguished Lecture Program (DLP) for delivering lectures, which enlighten/ enrich the knowledge of fellow professional engineers/ students. Our PES/IAS/PELS Jt. Chapter conducts every year various Distinguished Lecture Programs (DLPs). These are Flagship events of our Jt. Chapter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the above, our PES/ IAS/ PELS--Jt. Chapter is organizing the above PES-DLP in Hyderabad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More details about IEEE-Hyderabad Section &amp;nbsp;are at&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ieeehyd.org&quot;&gt;www.ieeehyd.org&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract of the above Lecture :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Power Electronic Convertors have &amp;nbsp;been used in power transmission systems for a long time now. Thyristor based devices have been used in HVDC transmission, static var compensators and Thyristor controlled series rectifiers. These days however power converter based devices are used in different applications under the umbrella of flexible ac transmission systems (FACTS). Moreover, multilevel converters are used HVDC light systems as they are more suitable for multi-terminal dc systems and sub-sea applications such as offshore wind power harnessing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The increasing number of installations of &amp;nbsp;Solar PV based rooftop systems are causing voltage and harmonic problems. Therefore much attention is needed before the penetration level of PV increases to a point where a total system collapse can occur. To solve this ever increasing problem, power electronic convertors are employed in power distribution systems to enhance power quality. The application of power electronics is clubbed under the umbrella of custom power (CP) through which customized power can be supplied to an individual customer or a group of customers. The different CP devices that employ power converters are distribution STATCOM (DSTATCOM), dynamic voltage restorer (DVR) and unified power quality conditioner (UPQC).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brief details of the Major Topics that will be covered in the above Lecture are as follows:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this Lecture it will be highlighted how these Custom Power Convertors / Devices can be used to clean power quality problems in power distribution grids and microgrids. Also, this lecture will cover converter structure, control and the applications for power quality improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ***&lt;/p&gt;
