&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A) Brief Details about this Program :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IEEE--PES/IAS/PELS Jt. Chapter, IEEE-Hyderabad Section, is organizing this Professional Development Program. We invite Industry Professionals, Young Professionals / Faculty in Academic Institutions and Research Scholars/ Students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Distinguished/ eminent persons who contributed to innovations, applications of &amp;nbsp;technology for the advancement of our society, are invited by our Jt. Chapter for an Interaction Meet and also for delivering Talks, which enlighten/ enrich the knowledge of fellow professional engineers/ students. In line with the above, our PES/ IAS/ PELS--Jt. Chapter is organizing the above Technical Talk / Lecture for&amp;nbsp; Professionals/ Young Professionals/&amp;nbsp; Students / Research Scholars in Hyderabad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More details about IEEE-Hyderabad Section &amp;nbsp;are at&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ieeehyd.org&quot;&gt;www.ieeehyd.org&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract of the above Lecture :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electricity is a great enabler for providing quality life and catalysing development. But it has many undesirable side effects too and electricity accidents is one such. Around 13,000 Indians die every year due to electricity accidents, and this number has been increasing over the years. The number of annual deaths in Telangana and Andhra Pradesh states is around 600 each. Most of the deaths occur in rural distribution systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IEEE Hyderabad has been working on this topic from 2015. Activities include training workshops, awareness programs, field studies, data analysis and technological innovations. The objective is to understand the cause of accidents and promote measures to reduce them. The first step was to understand &lt;strong&gt;why&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;where&lt;/strong&gt; the accidents occur, and &lt;strong&gt;who&lt;/strong&gt; are the victims. Based on this, some ideas on &lt;strong&gt;how&lt;/strong&gt; to prevent accidents are being developed. This includes a video on safety awareness, reports submitted to distribution companies, suggestions to regulatory bodies, training programs and field implementation of safe starter for agriculture pumpsets. We have also been collaborating with IEEE &amp;ndash; world-wide to learn from experience of other countries - both developed and developing. We are exploring innovations like high impedance relays and modification of pole structure to ensure timely tripping during ground faults.&lt;/p&gt;
