&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;****&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A) Brief Details about this Program:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IEEE--PES/IAS/PELS Jt. Chapter, IEEE-Hyderabad Section, is organizing this Professional Development Program. We invite Industry Professionals, Young Professionals / Faculty in Academic Institutions and Research Scholars/ Students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract of the above Lecture :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Power Plant equipment are very carefully designed and integrated for uninterrupted output with reliable and energy efficient operation. Electrical equipment are major functional sub-systems for the electricity produced from the power plant. Any interruption/ malfunction of their output will disrupt the power fed to the Utility grid and its power quality. This will lead to major disruption of&amp;nbsp; power supply to the end users in various sectors like Industries / Households/ Agriculture/ Transportation and others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this program the participants will be able to learn about the following information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Concepts, Operation and Design Aspects of various Electrical Equipment in Power Plants&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;The Protection Systems for various electrical equipment will also be explained in this presentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brief details of the Major Topics that will be covered in the above Program are as follows:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The focus will be on equipment like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;1) &lt;strong&gt;Electrical Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Turbo-Generators (TG) / Exciter &amp;amp; AVR/ Power Transformers/ Circuit Breakers and Isolators/ Distribution and Aux. Transformers/ Power Plant Grid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) Combined Gas and Steam Cycle &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3) Turbo Generators (TG): &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3-1) Design Aspects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3-2) Construction features:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stator/ Rotor/ Bearings/ Base frame/ Terminal arrangement/ Cooling System/ Exciter/ AVR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3-3) Operation, Control and Protection Systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3-4) TG Operating Conditions/ Performance Curves/ GT Output Curves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) TG Excitation Systems:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Automatic Regulators / Generator Control, Metering and Protections&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5)Generator Monitoring : Generator Protection Philosophy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6) Classification of Relays&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electromagnetic/ Solid state/ Microprocessor / Numerical / Non-electric (thermal, pressure, etc./&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advantages of numerical relays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7) Digital Generator Protection&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8) Transformers &amp;amp; Reactors : &lt;/strong&gt;Types and their Applications :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like Power Transformer/ Distribution Transformer/ Special Purpose Transformer/ Dry type Transformer/ Shunt Reactors /&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9) Power Systems :&lt;/strong&gt; Single Line Diagram (SLD) / Power System Basics/ Power System Stability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ***&lt;/p&gt;
